text: William Colclough (died c. 1414), of Newcastle-under-Lyme, Staffordshire and Calverhall, Shropshire, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Newcastle-under-Lyme in November 1384, 1385, 1386, January 1390, 1395 and January 1397.http://historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1386-1421/member/colclough- william-1414 ==References== Category:14th-century births Category:1414 deaths Category:English MPs November 1384 Category:English MPs 1385 Category:English MPs 1386 Category:English MPs January 1390 Category:English MPs 1395 Category:English MPs January 1397 Category:Members of the Parliament of England for Newcastle-under-Lyme Category:People from Shropshire
